user information to any third parties.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;All credit card transactions processed from this site use industry standard 128-bit encryption and we do not retain or store your credit card details.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Thinkwinetrade.com reserves the rights to record any conversations that might take place between the Buyer and the Seller (via phone, email, chat) and use it in cases of divergences.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If the customer does not wish to receive further offers or if it has any questions relating to privacy matters please contact us by email at support@thinkwinetrade.com.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;TWT team,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','Terms of Sales Buyers - Thinkwinetrade.com Online Wine Broker - Wine supplier &amp; delivery in Hong Kong - For Professionals only!','Wine supply in Hong Kong. On Trade and Off Trade market. Allows B2Bs to buy straight from the vineyards! Save 2 or 3 times the cost! Buy in bulk. No Importing License required! we do the Handling &amp; Shipping from the beginning to the end! Subscribe Now','Buy wine in Hong Kong, Hong Kong Wine Supplier, Buy French wine in Hong Kong, Bordeaux in Hong Kong, Burgundy in Hong Kong, Wine Supplier in Hong Kong, Import wine to Hong Kong, Import Fine Wine to Hong Kong, Wine agent in Hong Kong,'),(29,1,'Terms of Sales Buyers','&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;Thinkwinetrade.com (Online Wine Broker)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;Terms &amp;amp; Conditions of Sale&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;Support@thinkwinetrade.com&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;1. General Terms and Conditions&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Please read these terms of sale carefully before placing an order as they affect the rights and liabilities under the law and set out the terms under which Thinkwinetrade.com makes items available to the Buyer. These Terms supersede all previous oral or written representations, undertakings and agreements relating to the Goods.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Any variation to these Terms and Conditions (including any special Terms and conditions agreed between the parties) shall be inapplicable unless agreed in writing by the Thinkwinetrade.com.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Acceptance of sales order confirmation or pro forma invoice of the Goods shall be deemed conclusive evidence of the Buyer\'s acceptance of these Terms and Conditions.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If the interested entity does not agree to these Terms and Conditions and/or our Privacy and Cookies Policy, please do not register for or use the ThinkWineTrade.com Site. Please note that to use any of the services provided on the Thinkwinetrade.com.com Site, you are required to register as an authorized user.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Retain a copy of these terms and your order for future reference. These terms and conditions apply to all wines and other goods or services supplied by Thinkwinetrade.com to you.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;2. Definitions &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;In this document the following words shall have the following meanings:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&quot;Buyer&quot; means the firm or company who buys Goods from the Seller;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&quot;Seller&quot; means Thinkwinetrade.com at Thinkwinetrade.com 5 rue Lafaurie, 31400 Toulouse - FRANCE (Haute-Garonne)&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;“Customer” means a company or firm that registered on ThinkWineTreade.com site, receiving full access to the content of the site;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&quot;Goods&quot; means the articles to be supplied to the Buyer by the Seller;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&quot;Intellectual Property Rights&quot; means all patents, registered and unregistered designs, copyright, trademarks, know-how and all other forms of intellectual property wherever in the world enforceable;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&quot;List Price&quot; means the list of prices of the Goods maintained by the Seller as amended from time to time;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;“Contract” means the contract for sale and purchase of Goods in accordance with these Terms.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;“Orders” means a request by the Customer for Goods subject to these Terms.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;“Sample” means a small quantity (a bottle or more) from a wine category.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The headings in these Terms are for convenience only and shall not affect their interpretation.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;3. Product information&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Any description given or applied to the Goods is given by way of identification only and the use of such description shall not constitute a sale by description. For the avoidance of doubt, the Buyer hereby affirms that it does not in any way rely on any description when entering into the contract.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The Seller reserves the right to revise or change the style of labels and packaging at any time to make any changes in the specification of the Goods which are required to conform with any applicable health, safety or other statutory and/or E.U. requirements or, where the Goods are to be supplied to the Seller’s specification, which do not materially affect their quality or performance.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;While the Seller takes every precaution in the preparation of its catalogues, price lists and other literature, these documents are for the guidance of the Buyer only and statements therein shall not constitute representations by the Seller and the Seller shall not be bound by them. Any typographical, clerical or other error or omission in any sales literature, price list, acceptance of offer, invoice or other document or information issued by the Seller shall be subject to correction without any liability on the part of the Seller.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;4. Sample&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Thinkwinetrade.com encourages its potential and current Buyers to inspect and test the products sold. In order to accomplish that, the Buyer can order a small quantity of wine, called sample, pay the price of the bottle/bottles and the shipping tax and test the quality of the wine before ordering in bulk, with no strings attached.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Where a sample of the Goods is shown to and inspected &amp;nbsp;by the Buyer, the parties hereto accept that such a &amp;nbsp;sample is so shown and inspected for the sole purpose of enabling the Buyer to judge for itself the quality of the bulk, and not &amp;nbsp;so as to constitute a sale by sample.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;5. Order&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;An order is an offer to buy from the Seller. Nothing that the Seller does or says will amount to any acceptance of that offer until the Seller actually dispatch an item to the Buyer, at which point a contract will be made between the two parties. At any point up until then the Seller may decline to supply an item to a Buyer. If the Seller declines to supply an item to the Buyer and the Buyer has already paid for it, the Seller will provide a full refund of any amount already paid for that item in accordance with the company’s refund policy.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Where items are dispatched separately, the Seller’s acceptance of the order in respect of each item takes place when that item is dispatched.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;All goods are sold ex-works, in bulk (direct retail market), minimum quantity required to be bought being 50 cases / Pallet (each case contains 6 bottles of 75 cl).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;6. Availability&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;ThinkWineTrade.com does its best to ensure that all wines offered on the website are “currently available”, but availability is limited, especially concerning the rare, old wines, so all products offered are subject to availability. Despite that, Thinkwinetrade.com lets the Buyer know how many cases/bottles are left and the maximum amount that can be bought by one Buyer.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;7. Special Terms&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The Seller will notify the Buyer as to any special terms before the Buyer is requested to confirm any order. The notification will appear on the “pre-order sheet”, just before hitting the button “Validate”. At this moment, the Buyer has the right to either: accept the Terms and validate the order or to go back and modify its pallets. Placing an order following such notification will constitute acceptance of any special terms that the Seller have notified to the Buyer.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12px;&quot;&gt;8. Quality Guarantee and Policy&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Thinkwinetrade.com is committed to providing to its Buyers real authentic French products.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;All the producers are double checked before becoming Thinkwinetrade.com’s partners.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;A Certificate of Origin can be delivered, at request, by the Chamber of Commerce, the only governmental institutions entitled to do so.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Due the fact that providing quality is a must to Thinkwinetrade.com, the Buyer obliges itself that, once its order is received and inspected, it will fill in a form called “Review and Rating System at Delivery”. This form will be provided by the Seller to the Buyer’s account automatically after the order is processed and has to be filled in by the buyer in maximum 96 hours from receipt of the Goods. If not filled in, the Buyer’s account will be marked, without any previous notice.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Marking a buyer’s account signifies that the buyer will be able to see its purchases but will not be able to purchase new items from ThinkWineTrade.com.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If a wine is corked or faulty, Thinkwinetrade.com will offer a replacement or credit on the return of the bottle/bottles in question, accordingly to clause 15 “cancellation and returns” of this Terms.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;9. Price&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The price shall be that in the Seller\'s current website, or such other price as the parties may agree in writing. The prices of Goods stated in the Seller’s price list are subject to alteration without prior notice and will be reviewed at least once in a calendar year.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The prices shown on www.thinkwinetrade.com are only applicable to the companies/firms located in Hong Kong and registered with a valid HK CR registration number, which will be required in the registration process.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Prices listed for wines are quoted per bottle and per case and are exclusive of VAT or any other applicable taxes. (see text: http://www.customs.gov.hk/en/trade_facilitation/dutiable/types/)&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The price of an item does not include the delivery charge, which will depend on the delivery method you choose and the size of your order. The delivery charge will be calculated on the date you place your order.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If, by mistake, the Seller under-priced an item, it cannot be held responsible and obliged to provide that item to the Buyer at the wrong stated price. Instead, the Seller will notify the Buyer before dispatching the item: in case the Buyer agrees to the new price, the order will be processed and shipped; in case the Buyer does not accept, the order will be canceled and the amount paid reimbursed.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The final price (including the shipping costs) will be shown to the Buyer on the “pre-order sheet”, so the Buyer could have the chance to read it, understand it and either “Validate” the order or “Modify” it.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;10. Payment&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;the goods and shipping charges can be paid via paypal or bank transfer, only in Euros (€). In order to ease the communication between parties and erase any confusion that might appear, Think Wine Trade displays on its website the amount to be paid both in (€) Euros and (HK$) Hong Kong Dollars, before the Buyer places the order. The amount shown in HK$ is for informational purpose only and the exchange rate displayed is calculated at the current rate, updated every week. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;After the Buyer places the order and the full payment (consisting of the price of the items, shipping taxes and other taxes that might occur) is received, the Seller will review the necessary documentation and double-check the availability of the goods with its providers. The whole process will take a maximum of 15 days (for double check with vendors, grouping the product in single our single FR partner warehouse &amp;nbsp;address, palletising, French custom clearance, Shipping, HK custom clearance, HK partner shipping agent for pickup and check, HK warehouse, and HK delivery to customers) since the placement of the order (or change the amount of days as you consider) and, at the end of it, if everything is ok to go, the Seller will ship the products. After this time, the Buyer cannot amend its order. If, by any chance, some of the ordered products cannot be shipped because they are not on the producer’s inventory anymore, the Seller will inform the Buyer who will have to chose between changing its order or be reimbursed the amount paid for the unavailable goods. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;11. Delivery&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The delivery is assured by a combination of transportation companies selected by ThinWineTrade.com as for now we can identify 2 : Gondrand, Société de Transport Toulouse, 71 rue Jules Verne 31200 Toulouse + 33 (0)5 61 47 90 06 France &amp;amp; PLT Logistics (HK) Limited Unit C, 10/F, Unison Industrial Center, 27-31 Au Pui Wan Street, Shatin, N.T, Hong Kong +852 - 2297 0029, within 20-45 business days since placing the order.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The total shipping costs will be calculated after inserting the quantity bought and shown to the Buyer before validating the order and agreeing to the contract. The shipping costs do not include the buyer’s travelling insurance; in case the Buyer is requesting one, it can be charged an extra amount of money by the shipping company.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Unless otherwise agreed in writing, delivery of the Goods shall take place at the address specified by the Buyer within the timescale specified by the Seller. All goods must be signed for on delivery by an adult aged 18 years or over.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The delivery period specified by the Seller is an estimate only and shall not be of the essence of the contract. Buyer shall make all the necessary arrangements to take delivery of the Goods whenever they are tendered for delivery. If multiple delivery attempts are made to the provided delivery address and a competent recipient is not present to sign for the goods, or no effort is taken by the recipient to contact the courier to arrange re-delivery, the order will be returned to our warehouse. In this instance, a delivery surcharge may need to be paid by the customer in order for the goods to be re-delivered. The Company will contact you and provide you with a quote. The Company will not be liable for any loss or damage suffered by you through any delay in delivery.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The Seller shall use its reasonable endeavors to meet any stated delivery period or booked delivery date. In any event, time of delivery period or delivery booking shall not be of the essence and the Seller shall not be liable for any losses, costs, damages or expenses incurred by the Buyer or any third party arising directly or indirectly out of any failure to meet any estimated delivery period or date.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If the Seller is unable to commence delivery of the Goods for reasons beyond its control, then the Seller shall be entitled to place the Goods in storage until such times as delivery may be affected and the Buyer shall be liable for any expense associated with such storage.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If the Seller is unable to complete delivery whilst the Goods are in transit for reasons beyond its control, then the Buyer shall be liable for any wasted delivery expenses incurred by the Seller.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;12. Risks&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Risk in the Goods shall pass to the Buyer at the moment the Goods are dispatched from the Seller\'s premises. Where the Buyer chooses to collect the Goods itself, risk will pass when the Goods are entrusted to it or set aside for its collection, whichever happens first.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;13. Force Majeure&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The Seller shall not be liable for any delay or failure to perform any of its obligations if the delay or failure results from events or circumstances outside its reasonable control, including but not limited to acts of God, strikes, lock outs, accidents, war, fire, breakdown of plant or machinery or shortage or unavailability of raw materials from a natural source of supply, and the Seller shall be entitled to a reasonable extension of its obligations. If the delay persists for such time as the Seller considers unreasonable, it may, without liability on its part, terminate the contract.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;14. Title&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Title in the Goods shall not pass to the Buyer until the Seller has been paid in full for the Goods. The goods may be resold provided the proceeds of resale are paid to the Buyer to the extent necessary to discharge in full the amount due to the Seller.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;15. Cancellation and returns&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The Buyer has the right to cancel its order up until the moment the Seller dispatches the order. At this time, the Seller will cancel the order and refund the payment made by the Buyer.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;After the order has been dispatched, the Buyer has the right to use the “cancellation and returns” policy only if the delivered Goods are corky or faulty. This is due to the fact that wine are perishable goods and they require a great amount of resources and money to be sent back in safety.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;While receiving the order, the Buyer shall inspect the package for visible signs of transit damage before signing any delivery receipt document. In the event of visible signs of transit damage the Buyer must clearly sign the goods received as “damaged” on the delivery receipt document before signing. The Buyer shall then notify the Seller within 48 hours.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;After receiving the Goods, the Buyer shall inspect them immediately and notify the Seller through chat, email support@thinkwinetrade.com or tel.: ………… within 48 hours of receipt if there are any corky or faulty Goods. The Seller has the right to inspect itself the claims of the Buyer; In order to do that, the Buyer has to send the supposed bottle/bottles back to the Seller on its own costs. After receiving the Goods back, the Seller will examine them and if they are indeed corked or faulty due to Sellers’s fault, Thinkwinetrade.com will offer a replacement or credit. Where returned Goods are found to be damaged due to the Buyer\'s fault the Buyer will be liable for the cost of remedying such damage&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The faults that can be encountered in a wine are:&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;VISUAL FAULTS: Clarity, the Flower Disease, Shines, Fluidity, Effervescence, Stacker, Green Reflections, Grease, Oxidase Cassation, Brain Ferric, coppery Cassation, Protein Cassation.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;OLFACTORY FAULTS: Boucher smell (Tired, Maché, Eventé, Oxidized, maderized, Rancid), Reduced odor, Volatile acidity, Acetic Acid, Ethyl Acetate, vinegar smell, English or Banana Bonbon, Geranium, Lies smell, Pipi Cat, Green pepper, Rubber, Pharmaceutical Smells, mannitol, Tourne disease, bitterness, Rancid Butter, Fried Oil.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;TASTING FAULTS: Bitterness, Eventé, Vat / Cement, Metallic, Smart, Pourri, Lactic Pique.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;16. Applicable Law&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;These Terms and Conditions shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of FRANCE and any disputes will be decided only by the FRENCH COURTS.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The Seller shall not be liable in respect of any misrepresentation made by the Seller, its employees or agents to the Buyer as to the condition or quality of the Goods as far as FRENCH LAW allows or unless the representation is made or confirmed in writing by the Seller.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;17. Severability&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If any term or provision of these Terms and Conditions is held invalid, illegal or unenforceable for any reason by any court of competent jurisdiction such provision shall be severed and the remainder of the provisions hereof shall continue in full force and effect as if these Terms and Conditions had been agreed with the invalid, illegal or unenforceable provision eliminated.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;18. Waiver&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The failure by either party to enforce at any time or for any period any one or more of the Terms and Conditions herein shall not be a waiver of them or of the right at any time subsequently to enforce all Terms and Conditions of this Agreement.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;19. Miscellaneous&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The customer may not assign, sub-license or otherwise transfer any of its rights under these Terms and Conditions.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If any provision of these Terms and Conditions is found to be invalid by any court having competent jurisdiction, the invalidity of that provision will not affect the validity of the remaining provisions of these Terms and Conditions, which shall remain in full force and effect.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If the customer or the Seller breach these Terms and Conditions and Thinkwinetrade.com ignores it, Thinkwinetrade.com will still be entitled to use its rights and remedies at a later date or in any other situation where anyone breaches the Terms and Conditions.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Thinkwinetrade.com shall not be responsible for any breach of these Terms and Conditions caused by circumstances beyond its control.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;A person who is not a party to these Terms and Conditions shall have no right under the Contract to enforce any term of these Terms and Conditions but this shall not affect any right or remedy of a third party which exists or is available apart from that Act.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;20. Intellectual property&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The content of the www.thinkwinetrade.com site is protected by copyright, trade marks, database and other intellectual property rights. The customer or a third party may retrieve and display the content of the www.thinkwinetrade.com Site on a computer screen, store such content in electronic form on disk (but not any server or other storage device connected to a network) or print one copy of such content for personal, non-commercial use, provided keep intact all and any copyright and proprietary notices. The customer or a third party may not otherwise reproduce, modify, copy or distribute or use for commercial purposes any of the materials or content on the www.thinkwinetrade.com Site without written permission from Thinkwinetrade.com&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;No license is granted to you in these Terms and Conditions to use any trademark of www.thinkwinetrade.com, without limitation.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;21. Privacy Policy&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;When a customer registers its details on www.thinkwinetrade.com site or makes a purchase, the Seller collects personal information for processing and delivering the order. By registering those details on the Seller’s website, the customer consents Thinkwinetrade.com to maintain, record, hold, store and use personal data entered.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;This information may be used by www.thinkwinetrade.com to send offers which the Seller believes will interest you. In addition, www.thinkwinetrade.com may use the information gathered to make offers based on the customer’s wine preferences. Thinkwinetrade.com will not pass on the registered user information to any third parties.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;All credit card transactions processed from this site use industry standard 128-bit encryption and we do not retain or store your credit card details.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Thinkwinetrade.com reserves the rights to record any conversations that might take place between the Buyer and the Seller (via phone, email, chat) and use it in cases of divergences.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If the customer does not wish to receive further offers or if it has any questions relating to privacy matters please contact us by email at support@thinkwinetrade.com.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;TWT team,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','Terms of Sales Buyers - Thinkwinetrade.com Online Wine Broker - Wine supplier &amp; delivery in Hong Kong - For Professionals only!','Wine supply in Hong Kong. On Trade and Off Trade market. Allows B2Bs to buy straight from the vineyards! Save 2 or 3 times the cost! Buy in bulk. No Importing License required! we do the Handling &amp; Shipping from the beginning to the end! Subscribe Now','Buy wine in Hong Kong, Hong Kong Wine Supplier, Buy French wine in Hong Kong, Bordeaux in Hong Kong, Burgundy in Hong Kong, Wine Supplier in Hong Kong, Import wine to Hong Kong, Import Fine Wine to Hong Kong, Wine agent in Hong Kong,'),(29,3,'Terms of Sales Buyers','&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;Thinkwinetrade.com (Online Wine Broker)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;Terms &amp;amp; Conditions of Sale&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;Support@thinkwinetrade.com&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;1. General Terms and Conditions&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Please read these terms of sale carefully before placing an order as they affect the rights and liabilities under the law and set out the terms under which Thinkwinetrade.com makes items available to the Buyer. These Terms supersede all previous oral or written representations, undertakings and agreements relating to the Goods.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Any variation to these Terms and Conditions (including any special Terms and conditions agreed between the parties) shall be inapplicable unless agreed in writing by the Thinkwinetrade.com.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Acceptance of sales order confirmation or pro forma invoice of the Goods shall be deemed conclusive evidence of the Buyer\'s acceptance of these Terms and Conditions.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If the interested entity does not agree to these Terms and Conditions and/or our Privacy and Cookies Policy, please do not register for or use the ThinkWineTrade.com Site. Please note that to use any of the services provided on the Thinkwinetrade.com.com Site, you are required to register as an authorized user.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Retain a copy of these terms and your order for future reference. These terms and conditions apply to all wines and other goods or services supplied by Thinkwinetrade.com to you.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;2. Definitions &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;In this document the following words shall have the following meanings:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&quot;Buyer&quot; means the firm or company who buys Goods from the Seller;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&quot;Seller&quot; means Thinkwinetrade.com at Thinkwinetrade.com 5 rue Lafaurie, 31400 Toulouse - FRANCE (Haute-Garonne)&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;“Customer” means a company or firm that registered on ThinkWineTreade.com site, receiving full access to the content of the site;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&quot;Goods&quot; means the articles to be supplied to the Buyer by the Seller;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&quot;Intellectual Property Rights&quot; means all patents, registered and unregistered designs, copyright, trademarks, know-how and all other forms of intellectual property wherever in the world enforceable;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&quot;List Price&quot; means the list of prices of the Goods maintained by the Seller as amended from time to time;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;“Contract” means the contract for sale and purchase of Goods in accordance with these Terms.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;“Orders” means a request by the Customer for Goods subject to these Terms.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;“Sample” means a small quantity (a bottle or more) from a wine category.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The headings in these Terms are for convenience only and shall not affect their interpretation.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;3. Product information&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Any description given or applied to the Goods is given by way of identification only and the use of such description shall not constitute a sale by description. For the avoidance of doubt, the Buyer hereby affirms that it does not in any way rely on any description when entering into the contract.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The Seller reserves the right to revise or change the style of labels and packaging at any time to make any changes in the specification of the Goods which are required to conform with any applicable health, safety or other statutory and/or E.U. requirements or, where the Goods are to be supplied to the Seller’s specification, which do not materially affect their quality or performance.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;While the Seller takes every precaution in the preparation of its catalogues, price lists and other literature, these documents are for the guidance of the Buyer only and statements therein shall not constitute representations by the Seller and the Seller shall not be bound by them. Any typographical, clerical or other error or omission in any sales literature, price list, acceptance of offer, invoice or other document or information issued by the Seller shall be subject to correction without any liability on the part of the Seller.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;4. Sample&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Thinkwinetrade.com encourages its potential and current Buyers to inspect and test the products sold. In order to accomplish that, the Buyer can order a small quantity of wine, called sample, pay the price of the bottle/bottles and the shipping tax and test the quality of the wine before ordering in bulk, with no strings attached.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Where a sample of the Goods is shown to and inspected &amp;nbsp;by the Buyer, the parties hereto accept that such a &amp;nbsp;sample is so shown and inspected for the sole purpose of enabling the Buyer to judge for itself the quality of the bulk, and not &amp;nbsp;so as to constitute a sale by sample.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;5. Order&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;An order is an offer to buy from the Seller. Nothing that the Seller does or says will amount to any acceptance of that offer until the Seller actually dispatch an item to the Buyer, at which point a contract will be made between the two parties. At any point up until then the Seller may decline to supply an item to a Buyer. If the Seller declines to supply an item to the Buyer and the Buyer has already paid for it, the Seller will provide a full refund of any amount already paid for that item in accordance with the company’s refund policy.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Where items are dispatched separately, the Seller’s acceptance of the order in respect of each item takes place when that item is dispatched.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;All goods are sold ex-works, in bulk (direct retail market), minimum quantity required to be bought being 50 cases / Pallet (each case contains 6 bottles of 75 cl).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;6. Availability&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;ThinkWineTrade.com does its best to ensure that all wines offered on the website are “currently available”, but availability is limited, especially concerning the rare, old wines, so all products offered are subject to availability. Despite that, Thinkwinetrade.com lets the Buyer know how many cases/bottles are left and the maximum amount that can be bought by one Buyer.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;7. Special Terms&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The Seller will notify the Buyer as to any special terms before the Buyer is requested to confirm any order. The notification will appear on the “pre-order sheet”, just before hitting the button “Validate”. At this moment, the Buyer has the right to either: accept the Terms and validate the order or to go back and modify its pallets. Placing an order following such notification will constitute acceptance of any special terms that the Seller have notified to the Buyer.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12px;&quot;&gt;8. Quality Guarantee and Policy&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Thinkwinetrade.com is committed to providing to its Buyers real authentic French products.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;All the producers are double checked before becoming Thinkwinetrade.com’s partners.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;A Certificate of Origin can be delivered, at request, by the Chamber of Commerce, the only governmental institutions entitled to do so.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Due the fact that providing quality is a must to Thinkwinetrade.com, the Buyer obliges itself that, once its order is received and inspected, it will fill in a form called “Review and Rating System at Delivery”. This form will be provided by the Seller to the Buyer’s account automatically after the order is processed and has to be filled in by the buyer in maximum 96 hours from receipt of the Goods. If not filled in, the Buyer’s account will be marked, without any previous notice.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Marking a buyer’s account signifies that the buyer will be able to see its purchases but will not be able to purchase new items from ThinkWineTrade.com.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If a wine is corked or faulty, Thinkwinetrade.com will offer a replacement or credit on the return of the bottle/bottles in question, accordingly to clause 15 “cancellation and returns” of this Terms.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;9. Price&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The price shall be that in the Seller\'s current website, or such other price as the parties may agree in writing. The prices of Goods stated in the Seller’s price list are subject to alteration without prior notice and will be reviewed at least once in a calendar year.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The prices shown on www.thinkwinetrade.com are only applicable to the companies/firms located in Hong Kong and registered with a valid HK CR registration number, which will be required in the registration process.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Prices listed for wines are quoted per bottle and per case and are exclusive of VAT or any other applicable taxes. (see text: http://www.customs.gov.hk/en/trade_facilitation/dutiable/types/)&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The price of an item does not include the delivery charge, which will depend on the delivery method you choose and the size of your order. The delivery charge will be calculated on the date you place your order.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If, by mistake, the Seller under-priced an item, it cannot be held responsible and obliged to provide that item to the Buyer at the wrong stated price. Instead, the Seller will notify the Buyer before dispatching the item: in case the Buyer agrees to the new price, the order will be processed and shipped; in case the Buyer does not accept, the order will be canceled and the amount paid reimbursed.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The final price (including the shipping costs) will be shown to the Buyer on the “pre-order sheet”, so the Buyer could have the chance to read it, understand it and either “Validate” the order or “Modify” it.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;10. Payment&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;the goods and shipping charges can be paid via paypal or bank transfer, only in Euros (€). In order to ease the communication between parties and erase any confusion that might appear, Think Wine Trade displays on its website the amount to be paid both in (€) Euros and (HK$) Hong Kong Dollars, before the Buyer places the order. The amount shown in HK$ is for informational purpose only and the exchange rate displayed is calculated at the current rate, updated every week. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;After the Buyer places the order and the full payment (consisting of the price of the items, shipping taxes and other taxes that might occur) is received, the Seller will review the necessary documentation and double-check the availability of the goods with its providers. The whole process will take a maximum of 15 days (for double check with vendors, grouping the product in single our single FR partner warehouse &amp;nbsp;address, palletising, French custom clearance, Shipping, HK custom clearance, HK partner shipping agent for pickup and check, HK warehouse, and HK delivery to customers) since the placement of the order (or change the amount of days as you consider) and, at the end of it, if everything is ok to go, the Seller will ship the products. After this time, the Buyer cannot amend its order. If, by any chance, some of the ordered products cannot be shipped because they are not on the producer’s inventory anymore, the Seller will inform the Buyer who will have to chose between changing its order or be reimbursed the amount paid for the unavailable goods. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;11. Delivery&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The delivery is assured by a combination of transportation companies selected by ThinWineTrade.com as for now we can identify 2 : Gondrand, Société de Transport Toulouse, 71 rue Jules Verne 31200 Toulouse + 33 (0)5 61 47 90 06 France &amp;amp; PLT Logistics (HK) Limited Unit C, 10/F, Unison Industrial Center, 27-31 Au Pui Wan Street, Shatin, N.T, Hong Kong +852 - 2297 0029, within 20-45 business days since placing the order.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The total shipping costs will be calculated after inserting the quantity bought and shown to the Buyer before validating the order and agreeing to the contract. The shipping costs do not include the buyer’s travelling insurance; in case the Buyer is requesting one, it can be charged an extra amount of money by the shipping company.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Unless otherwise agreed in writing, delivery of the Goods shall take place at the address specified by the Buyer within the timescale specified by the Seller. All goods must be signed for on delivery by an adult aged 18 years or over.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The delivery period specified by the Seller is an estimate only and shall not be of the essence of the contract. Buyer shall make all the necessary arrangements to take delivery of the Goods whenever they are tendered for delivery. If multiple delivery attempts are made to the provided delivery address and a competent recipient is not present to sign for the goods, or no effort is taken by the recipient to contact the courier to arrange re-delivery, the order will be returned to our warehouse. In this instance, a delivery surcharge may need to be paid by the customer in order for the goods to be re-delivered. The Company will contact you and provide you with a quote. The Company will not be liable for any loss or damage suffered by you through any delay in delivery.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The Seller shall use its reasonable endeavors to meet any stated delivery period or booked delivery date. In any event, time of delivery period or delivery booking shall not be of the essence and the Seller shall not be liable for any losses, costs, damages or expenses incurred by the Buyer or any third party arising directly or indirectly out of any failure to meet any estimated delivery period or date.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If the Seller is unable to commence delivery of the Goods for reasons beyond its control, then the Seller shall be entitled to place the Goods in storage until such times as delivery may be affected and the Buyer shall be liable for any expense associated with such storage.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If the Seller is unable to complete delivery whilst the Goods are in transit for reasons beyond its control, then the Buyer shall be liable for any wasted delivery expenses incurred by the Seller.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;12. Risks&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Risk in the Goods shall pass to the Buyer at the moment the Goods are dispatched from the Seller\'s premises. Where the Buyer chooses to collect the Goods itself, risk will pass when the Goods are entrusted to it or set aside for its collection, whichever happens first.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;13. Force Majeure&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The Seller shall not be liable for any delay or failure to perform any of its obligations if the delay or failure results from events or circumstances outside its reasonable control, including but not limited to acts of God, strikes, lock outs, accidents, war, fire, breakdown of plant or machinery or shortage or unavailability of raw materials from a natural source of supply, and the Seller shall be entitled to a reasonable extension of its obligations. If the delay persists for such time as the Seller considers unreasonable, it may, without liability on its part, terminate the contract.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;14. Title&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Title in the Goods shall not pass to the Buyer until the Seller has been paid in full for the Goods. The goods may be resold provided the proceeds of resale are paid to the Buyer to the extent necessary to discharge in full the amount due to the Seller.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;15. Cancellation and returns&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The Buyer has the right to cancel its order up until the moment the Seller dispatches the order. At this time, the Seller will cancel the order and refund the payment made by the Buyer.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;After the order has been dispatched, the Buyer has the right to use the “cancellation and returns” policy only if the delivered Goods are corky or faulty. This is due to the fact that wine are perishable goods and they require a great amount of resources and money to be sent back in safety.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;While receiving the order, the Buyer shall inspect the package for visible signs of transit damage before signing any delivery receipt document. In the event of visible signs of transit damage the Buyer must clearly sign the goods received as “damaged” on the delivery receipt document before signing. The Buyer shall then notify the Seller within 48 hours.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;After receiving the Goods, the Buyer shall inspect them immediately and notify the Seller through chat, email support@thinkwinetrade.com or tel.: ………… within 48 hours of receipt if there are any corky or faulty Goods. The Seller has the right to inspect itself the claims of the Buyer; In order to do that, the Buyer has to send the supposed bottle/bottles back to the Seller on its own costs. After receiving the Goods back, the Seller will examine them and if they are indeed corked or faulty due to Sellers’s fault, Thinkwinetrade.com will offer a replacement or credit. Where returned Goods are found to be damaged due to the Buyer\'s fault the Buyer will be liable for the cost of remedying such damage&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The faults that can be encountered in a wine are:&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;VISUAL FAULTS: Clarity, the Flower Disease, Shines, Fluidity, Effervescence, Stacker, Green Reflections, Grease, Oxidase Cassation, Brain Ferric, coppery Cassation, Protein Cassation.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;OLFACTORY FAULTS: Boucher smell (Tired, Maché, Eventé, Oxidized, maderized, Rancid), Reduced odor, Volatile acidity, Acetic Acid, Ethyl Acetate, vinegar smell, English or Banana Bonbon, Geranium, Lies smell, Pipi Cat, Green pepper, Rubber, Pharmaceutical Smells, mannitol, Tourne disease, bitterness, Rancid Butter, Fried Oil.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;TASTING FAULTS: Bitterness, Eventé, Vat / Cement, Metallic, Smart, Pourri, Lactic Pique.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;16. Applicable Law&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;These Terms and Conditions shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of FRANCE and any disputes will be decided only by the FRENCH COURTS.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The Seller shall not be liable in respect of any misrepresentation made by the Seller, its employees or agents to the Buyer as to the condition or quality of the Goods as far as FRENCH LAW allows or unless the representation is made or confirmed in writing by the Seller.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;17. Severability&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If any term or provision of these Terms and Conditions is held invalid, illegal or unenforceable for any reason by any court of competent jurisdiction such provision shall be severed and the remainder of the provisions hereof shall continue in full force and effect as if these Terms and Conditions had been agreed with the invalid, illegal or unenforceable provision eliminated.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;18. Waiver&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The failure by either party to enforce at any time or for any period any one or more of the Terms and Conditions herein shall not be a waiver of them or of the right at any time subsequently to enforce all Terms and Conditions of this Agreement.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;19. Miscellaneous&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The customer may not assign, sub-license or otherwise transfer any of its rights under these Terms and Conditions.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If any provision of these Terms and Conditions is found to be invalid by any court having competent jurisdiction, the invalidity of that provision will not affect the validity of the remaining provisions of these Terms and Conditions, which shall remain in full force and effect.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If the customer or the Seller breach these Terms and Conditions and Thinkwinetrade.com ignores it, Thinkwinetrade.com will still be entitled to use its rights and remedies at a later date or in any other situation where anyone breaches the Terms and Conditions.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Thinkwinetrade.com shall not be responsible for any breach of these Terms and Conditions caused by circumstances beyond its control.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;A person who is not a party to these Terms and Conditions shall have no right under the Contract to enforce any term of these Terms and Conditions but this shall not affect any right or remedy of a third party which exists or is available apart from that Act.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;20. Intellectual property&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The content of the www.thinkwinetrade.com site is protected by copyright, trade marks, database and other intellectual property rights. The customer or a third party may retrieve and display the content of the www.thinkwinetrade.com Site on a computer screen, store such content in electronic form on disk (but not any server or other storage device connected to a network) or print one copy of such content for personal, non-commercial use, provided keep intact all and any copyright and proprietary notices. The customer or a third party may not otherwise reproduce, modify, copy or d